Package com.github.tcn.plexi.paginators

Class Paginator.Builder<T extends Paginator.Builder<T,​V>,​V extends Paginator>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.tcn.plexi.paginators.Paginator.Builder<T,​V>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SearchPaginator.Builder, SearchSubmenu.Builder
    Enclosing class:
    Paginator
    public abstract static class Paginator.Builder<T extends Paginator.Builder<T,​V>,​V extends Paginator>
extends java.lang.Object
    An extendable frame for a chain-method builder that constructs a specified type of Menu. Conventionally, implementations of Menu should have a static nested class called Builder, which extends this superclass: 
    
 public class MyMenu extends Menu
 {
     // Menu Code

    public static class Builder extends Menu.Builder<Builder, MyMenu>
     {
         // Builder Code
     }
 }
    "Implementation Note:"
    This is pretty much a clone of Menu.Builder and because of that, I felt it necessary to not only use his javadoc, but keep him as co-author of this particular builder class
